{"data":{"page":{"id":"da327c0e-a475-5592-94b5-bb87908702de","html":"<p class=\"align-center\">\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\"http://work.joanmira.com/webs/proyecto2025/\" target=\"_blank\">Launch archived template without DB</a></p>\n<p>Proyecto2025 contacted us (Webmarket) to build a website to feature their real state properties and allow customers to search them. They also wanted a flexible system to edit, add or remove properties easily.</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 101%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b078219f3586dca4319e109b3384e586/877ff/1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b078219f3586dca4319e109b3384e586/d2504/1.jpg 500w,\n/static/b078219f3586dca4319e109b3384e586/877ff/1.jpg 1000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>At this point, I didn’t have a system or CMS with this sort of functionality. The open source options available at that time were also very insufficient for the requirements, so I decided to build my own bespoke solution. I called it INMOFlash, because it was based in Flash, PHP and MySQL.</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.3%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/8058bf6af20bdd919eefad4125232e42/877ff/2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8058bf6af20bdd919eefad4125232e42/d2504/2.jpg 500w,\n/static/8058bf6af20bdd919eefad4125232e42/877ff/2.jpg 1000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>The combination of using Flash for the UI and MySQL and PHP for the backend was a winning solution in terms of creativity and UX. Years after, I realised that Flash was not the best option for SEO, therefore this solution didn’t have a very long future, but at the time, it was quite impressive and flexible.</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1317px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 67.42596810933941%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"3\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/03b7f720dde47d7d32743abb552da1b3/b4400/3.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/03b7f720dde47d7d32743abb552da1b3/5f2bb/3.jpg 500w,\n/static/03b7f720dde47d7d32743abb552da1b3/15635/3.jpg 1000w,\n/static/03b7f720dde47d7d32743abb552da1b3/b4400/3.jpg 1317w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1317px) 100vw, 1317px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-res